        }
      ],
      "text": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">A patient with Hereditary Fructose Intolerance (HFI) presents with symptoms indicative of the condition. Consider the following statements:</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Assertion (A): Hereditary fructose intolerance (HFI) results in accumulation of fructose-6-phosphate, which is the reason behind organomegaly seen in this condition.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Reasoning (R): Above condition is due to aldolase B deficiency.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Choose the correct option regarding the assertion and reasoning.</span></span></span></p>",
      "unique_key": "Q4370866",
      "question_audio": null,
      "question_video": null,
      "map_id": 30026,
      "difficulty_level": "difficult",
      "subjects_id": [
        1
      ],
      "solution": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Ans. C) A is wrong, but R is a right statement</span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Option C:</span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">In<strong> Hereditary Fructose Intolerance (HFI),</strong> the <strong>deficiency </strong>of the enzyme <strong>aldolase B</strong> leads to the <strong>accumulation of fructose-1-phosphate,</strong> <strong>not fructose-6-phosphate</strong>. Aldolase B is crucial for the metabolism of<strong> fructose to glyceraldehyde and dihydroxyacetone</strong> <strong>phosphate</strong> in the <strong>liver, kidney, and intestine</strong>. The<strong> accumulation of fructose-1-phosphate</strong> is <strong>toxic</strong> and results in symptoms such as <strong>hypoglycemia, vomiting, and failure to thrive, </strong>as well as<strong> liver and renal dysfunction</strong> which can contribute to <strong>organomegaly.</strong> Therefore, the <strong>assertion is incorrect </strong>regarding the <strong>specific fructose phosphate</strong> that accumulates, while the <strong>reasoning correctly</strong> <strong>identifies aldolase B deficiency</strong> as the cause of<strong> HFI.</strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">&nbsp;<u>Explanation:</u></span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Option A.&nbsp; A is right but R is a wrong statement:</span></strong><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\"> This option is<strong> incorrect </strong>because the <strong>assertion incorrectly identifies</strong> the metabolite that accumulates in HFI.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Option B. A as well as R are right and R is a correct explanation of A:</span></strong><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\"> This option is <strong>incorrect </strong>because the <strong>assertion incorrectly</strong> states the<strong> metabolite </strong>involved in<strong> HFI.</strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Option D.&nbsp; A and R both are wrong:</span></strong><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\"> This option is <strong>incorrect</strong> because the <strong>reasoning statement</strong> about <strong>aldolase B deficiency </strong>is <strong>correct.</strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><strong><u><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Educational Objective:</span></u></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n\t<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">During <strong>metabolism </strong>of <strong>fructose</strong>, fructose &rarr; <strong>fructose-1-phosphate</strong> (enzyme fructokinase) &rarr; <strong>glyceraldehyde</strong> and <strong>dihydroxyacetone phosphate</strong> (aldolase B enzyme). </span></span></span></li>\r\n\t<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\"><strong>Deficiency </strong>of this <strong>aldolase B</strong> &rarr; <strong>accumulation of fructose-1-phosphate</strong> in various<strong> organs</strong> leading to <strong>organomegaly.</strong></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><strong><u><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Ref</span></u></strong><strong><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">: Harper 30/e: p 202,205.</span></strong></span></span></p>",
